<title>Xen Software: xen-shell downloads</title>
<div class="contentbox-title-shading">Xen Shell Stable Releases</div>
	<div class="contentbox-noshading">
	<p>The most recent version of the Xen Shell is version v1.9, and you can download it via the following link:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="xen-shell-1.9.tar.gz">xen-shell-1.9.tar.gz</a></li>
<li><a href="xen-shell-1.9.tar.gz.asc">xen-shell-1.9.tar.gz.asc</a> -1k (GPG signature which may be validated using <a href="http://www.steve.org.uk/contact/steve_kemp.gpg">my</a> <a href="http://www.gnu.org/software/gnump3d/steve_kemp.gpg">public</a> <a href="http://db.debian.org/fetchkey.cgi?fingerprint=DB1FF3FB1D08FC01ED222243C0CFC6B3CD4C0D9D">key</a>).</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>Binary packages of the project are included in the <a href="http://www.debian.org/">Debian GNU/Linux Project</a>, in both the Unstable and Testing branches.</p>
<p>I maintain a package for Debian stable upon my <a href="http://apt.steve.org.uk/">personal apt repository</a>.</p>

<p>If you'd like to be informed of new releases please consider subscribing to <a href="http://freshmeat.net/projects/xen-shell">xen-shell freshmeat project</a> - if you did this it would be appreciated if you would <a href="http://freshmeat.net/rate/611.8/">rate the project</a>.</p>

	</div>
      </div>


